\pagebreakNum

### Green Dragonflight

*"You are bound to the waking Dream of Creation. Nature is your realm, and all things have caught glimpses of the Emerald Dream when they sleep. You see them all, Ysera. And they see you, though they may not know it. Like the Life-Binder, you touch all living beings, and sing to them the songs of creation and interconnectedness."*

<div style="text-align:Right">

— *Eonar's blessing of the Green Aspect*

</div>

The green dragonflight consists of dragons adorned with vibrant, green scales -- earning them their second moniker as the *Emerald Dragonflight*. 

During the ordering of Azeroth, the titan Eonar charged Ysera and her flight with upholding the natural balance of both Azeroth and the Emerald Dream; a pristine spirit-realm of nature and magic that exists far beyond the boundaries of the physical world. It is through this charge that the green dragons keep their affinity for the wilds.

***Protectors of Nature.*** When dealing with mortals, green dragons primarily only come into conflict with those who would attempt to corrupt or destroy nature. In this sense, much like the red dragons, they are among the most approachable of the dragonflights. To this end, they have many a time sought the help of druids to aid in their task, and to this day keep a close connection with such groups -- the Cenarion Circle in particular.

***Solitary Lives.*** Given the task placed upon them and their ties to the Emerald Dream, it is not surprising that green dragons highly reclusive; exceedingly difficult for mere mortals to find on their own. They are peaceful, meditative, and said to be spending most of their time in slumber and quiet contemplation. 

\columnbreak

***Seeding the Great Trees.*** Following the Great Sundering at the end of the War of the Ancients, the green Dragon Aspect Ysera played part in seeding a colossal tree within the new Well of Eternity. The tree became known as Nordrassil, the Crown of the Heavens -- and with its branches as saplings, several more trees were scattered across Azeroth. 

These were the Great Trees, five of them in total. They were not planted with Ysera's approval, however, nor did they receive her blessing as Nordrassil once had. And so, as the trees came to tower over the lands, their roots dug deep, one tree fell an ill fate. In Northrend, the great tree Andrassil had reached deep enough into the earth to touch the subterranean prison of Yogg'saron. 

***The Seeping Nightmare.*** As Yogg'saron touched the roots of Andrassil, without the dragons' protection, corruption quickly seeped into the tree. Though it was a heartbreaking task for the druids of the Cenarion Circle, the tree was destroyed -- renamed Vordrassil, the Broken Crown -- and the corruption thought stopped. 

The Great Trees would all act as portals; each one an anchoring point for the druids and green dragons alike to travel between Azeroth and the Emerald Dream, as well as a grove under the dragonflight's protection. 

Unknown to them all, however, was the darkness that had already taken root within the Emerald Dream. Yogg'saron, and the other Old Gods with it, used the Great Trees to allow their influence to reach beyond the mortal world. Heralded by a corrupting mist that spread out across the land, and by its eponymous Nightmare Lord, swathes of the Dream were twisted beyond any resemblance of its verdant self and corrupted into a waking Nightmare. 


<img src="https://www.gmbinder.com/images/k0wknyx.jpg" style="position: absolute; background:darkblue; top:570px; left:-50px; width:1050px;" />
<img src="https://www.gmbinder.com/images/C2bOp8u.png" style="position:absolute; top:-300px; left:0px; height:1030px; transform:scaleY(-1);" />

