<img src='https://www.gmbinder.com/images/NO1EQoX.png' style='position:absolute; left:0px; bottom:0px; width:900px; transform:scaleY(-1)' />

<div class='footnote footnote-white'>DRAGONS | Red Dragonflight</div>
<div class="pageLetter">D</div>

\pagebreakNum

### Lesser Dragonflights
Outside of the five greater dragonflights exists a number of outliers; all true dragons, with all the vast power and intellect that implies, but each of them outside of the charge of the Titans that has long empowered them.

These lesser dragonflights are all connected in some way to the five true flights, but each is distinct and unique in their own regard, eking out a place in the world that separates them from the true dragonflights. For better or worse, these lesser dragonflights are races unto themselves, and can be as if not more dangerous than the prime dragonflights.
 
#### Infinite Dragonflight
Appearing as invasive forces throughout the timeways as twisted inverses of the bronze dragonflight, the mysterious infinite dragonflight appear to their bronze foes as insane and extremely dangerous terrorists threatening the flows of history itself.

The infinite flight traverse history, appearing through hijacked timeways at important moments in history to disrupt and change the passage of time, seeking to avert some distant future that they consider unfavourable. Their origin is unknown, as are their motivations or base of operations; all that is known is that they are a threat to all of time, and the enemy to all life.

***The Infinite Aspect.*** Seemingly equal in power to the five true Dragon Aspects is the mysterious, unseen leader of the infinite flight. From a distant, broken, locked future timeline, this dragon of immense power directs the rest of their flight to influence past events with zealous fervour, as though desperate to change the future.
 
#### Netherwing Dragonflight
The netherwing dragonflight were born from black dragon eggs brought by Deathwing onto the orc homeworld Draenor -- shortly before it was destroyed. As the calamity tore the planet asunder, the volatile powers of the Twisting Nether saw the eggs hatch into shimmering, translucent beings; half there, half not.

Now fairly numerous, these world-weary dragons have lived hard lives since Outland's collapse, facing threats of enslavement or extinction at the hands of orcs and demons, before seeing their rapid lives burn out like too-bright stars in the dim sky. Like much else in Outland, they live lives of tragedy; nasty, brutish and short lives marred by the irony of their own creation, as dragons that were meant to be stockpiles of black eggs, and ended up being close to nothing at all.

They are wary of the world around them, and mistrusting of strangers, but the bonds they create with the few mortals they trust are eternal, and forged by dragonfire; for although they are composed of wild energy, dragons they are, and they are pleased to be recognized as such.
 
\columnbreak

<div style='margin-top:30px;'></div>

#### Twilight Dragonflight
The culmination of years of study and experimentation by the consort to Deathwing, Sintharia, the twilight flight was crafted from the blood of all flights for one purpose alone; they are superweapons, vitriolic masses of unstable energy in dragon form that are able to release overwhelming power upon the foes of their masters, the black dragonflight. Their very existence is chaos, their bodies radiating the same twisted energies that saw their creation as they shift back and forth between the material world and a harrowing plane of existence known as the Realm of Twilight.

The greatest danger in encountering these creatures is their uncontrollable nature. Though they are loyal to Deathwing, they are prone to cowardice, outbursts and mockery when placed in the command of anyone else. This, combined with the extremely unstable nature of their bodies, makes being around one a dangerous risk even for allies. When they die, and even sometimes when they do not, their bodies are known to suddenly and violently explode with life-extinguishing energy, taking with them a sizeable chunk of the environment.

___
> ##### Chromatic Dragonflight
> One of Nefarion's earliest experiments was attempting to condense the powers of the five greater dragonflights into a single creation, to be known as the chromatic dragonflight. These experiments were largely considered failures; many whelps died before hatching, and those that survived were unstable, short-lived, volatile, and/or deformed. One of the very few successes of these experiments was the drakeadon, a semi-draconic beast.

