> ## Netherwing Dragonwhelp <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?0;13;49;4;12;20;0;10;0;10;0;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;;1;4;;;;;;;;;;3;;;;;;;;15;;;;;;;;;;;1;0;1;3; -->
>*Small dragon, neutral*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 13 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 49 (9d6 + 18)
> - **Speed** 30 ft., fly 60 ft.
>___
> |  STR  |  DEX  |  CON  |  INT  |  WIS  |  CHA  |
> |:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> |15 (+2)|10 (+0)|14 (+2)|12 (+1)|11 (+0)|14 (+2)|
>___
> - **Saving Throws** Dex +2, Con +4 , Wis +2, Cha +4
> - **Skills** Perception +2, Survival +2
> - **Condition Immunities** restrained, stunned
> - **Senses** blindsight 10 ft., darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12
> - **Languages** Common, Draconic
> - **Challenge** 1 (200 XP)
> ___
>
> ### Actions
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 7 (1d10 + 2) piercing damage plus 3 (1d6) force damage.
>
> ***Nether Breath (Recharge 5-6).*** The dragonwhelp exhales violent nether energy in a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area takes 10 (4d4) force damage.
> <br/>    Any creature damaged by this breath is outlined in faint energy until the end of the dragonwhelp's next turn and can't benefit from being invisible.
>
> ***Change Shape.*** The dragonwhelp magically transforms into any humanoid that is Medium or Small, while retaining its game statistics (other than its size). This transformation ends if the dragon is reduced to 0 hit points or uses a bonus action to end it.
>
> ### Reactions
> ***Intangible Presence (Recharge 5-6).*** When hit with an attack the dragonwhelp can turn partially intangible, gaining damage resistance against bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from attacks (including the triggering attack) until the beginning of its next turn. 
> <br/>    For the duration, whenever the dragonwhelp is damaged by a spell, it takes an additional point of damage per damage die.


