> ## Netherwing Dragon <!-- https://wc5e-cr-calculator.frogvall.com/?2;17;200;11;19;50;46;40;46;40;46;0;0;0;0;0;0;;;;1;4;;;;;;;1;;1;3;;;;;;;;15;;;;;;;4;3;3;14;1;0;1;3;Fel%20Flame;Shadow%20Bolt;Ray%20of%20Sickness;Hunger%20of%20Hadar;Sickening%20Radiance -->
> *Huge dragon, neutral*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 17 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 200 (16d12 + 96)
> - **Speed** 40 ft., fly 80 ft.
>___
> |  STR  |  DEX  |  CON  |  INT  |  WIS  |  CHA  |
> |:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|:-----:|
> |23 (+6)|10 (+0)|22 (+6)|16 (+3)|15 (+2)|22 (+6)|
>___
> - **Saving Throws** Dex +5, Con +11, Wis +7, Cha +11
> - **Skills**  Perception +7, Survival +7
> - **Condition Immunities** restrained, stunned
> - **Senses** blindsight 10 ft., darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 17
> - **Languages** Common, Draconic
> - **Challenge** 15 (13,000 XP)
> ___
>
> ***Innate Spellcasting.*** The dragon's innate spellcasting ability is Charisma (spell save DC 19, +11 to hit with spell attacks). It can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:
> 
> At will: *dancing lights*, *detect magic*, ✦*fel flame*, <br/>    *message*, ✦*shadow bolt*
> <br/> 3/day each: *darkness*, *hunger of hadar*, *invisibility*, *ray <br/>    of sickness*
> <br/> 1/day each: *enemies abound* ^XGE^, *sickening radiance* ^XGE^
> 
> ***Legendary Resistance (3/Day).*** If the dragon fails a saving throw, it can choose to succeed instead.
>
> ***Nether Burn Aura.***  Every wounded enemy creature within 30 feet of the dragon must make a DC 19 Constitution saving throw at the start of their turn, taking 10 (3d6) necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The dragon can use its Frightful Presence. It then makes two attacks: one with its bite and one with its claw.
>
> ***Bite.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +11 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. *Hit:* 17 (2d10 + 6) piercing damage plus 10 (3d6) force damage.
>
> ***Claw.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +11 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 13 (2d6 + 6) slashing damage.
>
> ***Tail Sweep.*** The dragon swings its tail, and every creature within 15 feet of it must make a DC 19 Dexterity saving throw. On a failed saving throw, a creature takes 15 (2d8 + 6) bludgeoning damage and is knocked prone. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage and isn’t knocked prone. 
>
> ***Frightful Presence.*** Each creature of the dragon's choice that is within 120 feet of the dragon and aware of it must succeed on a DC 19 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's saving throw is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to the dragon's Frightful Presence for the next 24 hours.
>
> ***Nether Breath (Recharge 5-6).*** The dragon exhales violent nether energy in a 60-foot cone. Each creature takes 25 (10d4) force damage.
> <br/>    Any creature damaged by this breath is outlined in faint energy until the end of the dragon's next turn and can't benefit from being invisible.
>
> ***Change Shape.*** The dragon magically transforms into any humanoid that is Medium or Small, while retaining its game statistics (other than its size). This transformation ends if the dragon is reduced to 0 hit points or uses a bonus action to end it.
>
> ### Reactions
> ***Intangible Presence (Recharge 5-6).*** When hit with an attack the dragon can turn partially intangible, gaining damage resistance against bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage from attacks (including the triggering attack) until the beginning of its next turn. 
> <br/>    For the duration, whenever the dragon is damaged by a spell, it takes an additional point of damage per damage die.
>
> ### Legendary Actions
> The dragon can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The dragon regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.
> 
> **Decrepify.** A creature within 60 feet that the dragon can 
<br/>    see must make a DC 19 Dexterity save. On a failure, 
<br/>    their movement speed is reduced to 0 feet until the 
<br/>    end of the dragon's next turn.
> <br/> **Drain Energy.** The dragon drains the ambient energy 
<br/>    around it, regaining a use of Intangible Presence. 
<br/>    Each creature concentrating on a spell within 15 feet 
<br/>    of the dragon must make a DC 10 Constitution 
<br/>    saving throw or lose the spell.
> <br/> **Nether Drain (Costs 2 Actions).** Each creature within 
<br/>    30 feet of the dragon who took damage from its 
<br/>    Nether Burn Aura or Nether Breath since the 
<br/>    beginning of its last turn must make a DC 19 
<br/>    Constitution save, taking 10 (3d6) necrotic damage 
<br/>    on a failed save or half as much on a successful one. 
<br/>    The dragon regains hit points equal to the necrotic 
<br/>    damage dealt.
> <br/> **Wing Attack (Costs 2 Actions).** The dragon beats its 
<br/>    wings. Each creature within 10 feet of the dragon 
<br/>    must succeed on a DC 19 Dexterity saving throw or 
<br/>    take 13 (2d6 + 6) bludgeoning damage and be 
<br/>    knocked prone. The dragon can then fly up to half its 
<br/>    flying speed.

